{"word":"ἐφηγέομαι","slug":"ἐφηγέομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n45719\" key=\"e)fhge/omai\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ἐφηγ-έομαι</orth>, <sense id=\"n45719.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">lead to</tr_> a place: c. dat. pers., esp. as <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Att.\">Att.</a></gram> </gramGrp> law-term, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">lead the magistrate to a place where a criminal lay concealed</tr_>, whom the informer durst not seize himself, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0014.tlg022.perseus-grc1:26\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ D.\">D.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">22.26</biblScope></bibl>, cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0014.tlg026.perseus-grc1:9\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">26.9</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0542.tlg001:8:50\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Poll.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">8.50</biblScope></bibl>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}